  "texts": [
    "Moreover, spoken languages and sign languages diverge not only in their underlying structural and grammatical systems but also in their modes of expression, vocal for spoken languages and gestural for sign languages respectively.",
    "The intricacy of sign language as a visual language is evidenced in its reliance on an array of handshapes, facial expressions, and body movements to convey meaning [5][6][7].",
    "Additionally, effectively translating and learning sign language, like Auslan, requires not only an understanding of the signs themselves, but also an appreciation of the unique cultural and contextual nuances inherent in sign language communication.",
    "These nuances include the way emotions are expressed, idiomatic expressions specific to the Deaf community, and the broader cultural context that informs how sign language is used.",
    "This complexity significantly increases the difficulty of learning and translating sign language, especially in scenarios where either children or parents are deaf or hearing loss.However, current efforts in Auslan translation applications primarily exhibit three major shortcomings."
  ]
}